@tex
$$\eqalign{
    Y &= \overline{A}\,\overline{B}\,C\,D +
         \overline{A}\,B\,C\overline{D} +
         \overline{A}\,B\,C\,D +
         A\,\overline{B}\,\overline{C}\overline{D}\cr
      &+ A\,\overline{B}\,\overline{C}\,D +
         A\,\overline{B}\,C\,\overline{D} +
         A\,\overline{B}\,C\,D
}$$
@end tex
Use theorems T6--T8, Commutativity, Associativity, and Distributivity to
rewrite the equation:
@tex
$$\eqalign{
Y &= C\,D\bullet(\overline{A}\,B + \overline{A}\,\overline{B}) +
     A\,\overline{B}\bullet(\overline{C}\,D + \overline{C}\,\overline{D}) +
     A\,\overline{B}\bullet(C\,D + C\,\overline{D}) +
     \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D}\cr
}$$
@end tex
Apply theorems T6--T8 and T10 to rewrite:
@tex
$$\eqalign{
Y &= C\,D\bullet(\overline{A}) + A\,\overline{B}\bullet(\overline{C}) +
     A\,\overline{B}\bullet(C) + \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D}\cr
  &= \overline{A}\,C\,D + A\,\overline{B}\,\overline{C} + A\,\overline{B}\,C +
     \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D}\cr
  &= \overline{A}\,C\,D + \overline{B}\bullet(A\,C + A\,\overline{C}) +
     \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D}\cr
  &= \overline{A}\,C\,D + \overline{B}\bullet(A) +
     \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D}\cr
  &= \overline{A}\,C\,D + A\,\overline{B} + \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D}\cr
}$$
@end tex
At this point, none of our theorems will further minimize this without expanding
an implicant. Use the Null Element theorem (T2') to expand an implicant
that will be easy to factor with an additional @math{B} literal.
@tex
$$\eqalign{
Y &= \overline{A}\,C\,D\bullet(B + 1) + A\,\overline{B} +
     \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D}\cr
  &= \overline{A}\,B\,C\,D + \overline{A}\,B\,C\,\overline{D} +
     A\,\overline{B} + \overline{A}\,C\,D\cr
  &= \overline{A}\,B\bullet(C\,D + C\,\overline{D}) + A\,\overline{B} +
     \overline{A}\,C\,D\cr
  &= \overline{A}\,B\,C + A\,\overline{B} + \overline{A}\,C\,D\cr
Y &= A\,\overline{B} + \overline{A}\,B\,C + \overline{A}\,C\,D
}$$
@end tex
